cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a framework for cross-modal biometric matching of voices and faces, which involves computer vision (faces) and natural language processing (voices). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves multimodal learning, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves biometric matching, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
